    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-08T04:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-08T04:30:00-05:00" n="566"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.01/198: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Bombay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Donovan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bombay</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-08T15:00:00+05:30"
                            >June 8, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 8—2:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>424. This office had no correspondence whatever either direct or indirect with
                    the Maharaja of Indore on this subject. Your 216.<note n="85" xml:id="d566fn85">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> Neither I nor any member of my staff
                    were associated in any way with the preparation of this letter.</p>
                <p>At the request of a friend who is a press correspondent, I delivered to Reuters a
                    sealed cover which unknown to me contained text of Maharaja’s letter. I did this
                    as a personal favor to save time for my friend since I happened to be passing by
                    Reuters office. Later that day I was informed by my friend of contents of cover.
                    See my airmail despatch 567, June 3.<note n="86" xml:id="d566fn86">Not
                        printed.</note> This despatch and my 400<note n="87" xml:id="d566fn87"
                        >Telegram dated May 29, 1 p.m., <ref target="#pg_665">p. 665</ref>.</note>
                    were written after full text of letter had appeared Bombay <hi rend="italic"
                        >Times of India</hi> May 29.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Donovan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
